SIMPLE: sermonize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sermonize
<hw>Ser"mon*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sermonized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Sermonizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To compose or write a sermon or sermons; to preach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inculcate rigid rules.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sermonize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sermonize
<hw>Ser"mon*ize</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To preach or discourse to;
to affect or influence by means of a sermon or of sermons.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which of us shall sing or <qex>sermonize</qex> the other fast
asleep?</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sermonizer</ent>⟦br⟧
